  {title: "Hidden Heart Valentine's Pound Cake", ingredients_data: [{"id"=>9070, "aisle"=>"Produce", "image"=>"cherries.jpg", "consistency"=>"solid", "name"=>"cherry", "original"=>"½ teaspoon – 1 tablespoon Natural Cherry Extract/Flavoring", "originalString"=>"½ teaspoon – 1 tablespoon Natural Cherry Extract/Flavoring", "originalName"=>"– 1 tablespoon Natural Cherry Extract/Flavoring", "amount"=>0.5, "unit"=>"teaspoon", "meta"=>[], "metaInformation"=>[], "measures"=>{"us"=>{"amount"=>0.5, "unitShort"=>"tsps", "unitLong"=>"teaspoons"}, "metric"=>{"amount"=>0.5, "unitShort"=>"tsps", "unitLong"=>"teaspoons"}}}, {"id"=>10711111, "aisle"=>"Baking", "image"=>"food-coloring.png", "consistency"=>"solid", "name"=>"food coloring", "original"=>"1/8 teaspoon Pink Food Coloring", "originalString"=>"1/8 teaspoon Pink Food Coloring", "originalName"=>"Pink Food Coloring", "amount"=>0.125, "unit"=>"teaspoon", "meta"=>[], "metaInformation"=>[], "measures"=>{"us"=>{"amount"=>0.125, "unitShort"=>"tsps", "unitLong"=>"teaspoons"}, "metric"=>{"amount"=>0.125, "unitShort"=>"tsps", "unitLong"=>"teaspoons"}}}, {"id"=>99040, "aisle"=>"Gluten Free", "image"=>"chocolate-cake.jpg", "consistency"=>"solid", "name"=>"gf chocolate cake mix", "original"=>"1 box Favorite Chocolate Pound Cake mix", "originalString"=>"1 box Favorite Chocolate Pound Cake mix", "originalName"=>"Favorite Chocolate Pound Cake mix", "amount"=>1.0, "unit"=>"box", "meta"=>[], "metaInformation"=>[], "measures"=>{"us"=>{"amount"=>1.0, "unitShort"=>"box", "unitLong"=>"box"}, "metric"=>{"amount"=>1.0, "unitShort"=>"box", "unitLong"=>"box"}}}, {"id"=>18133, "aisle"=>"Bakery/Bread", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg", "consistency"=>"solid", "name"=>"pound cake", "original"=>"1 box Favorite Vanilla or Butter Pound Cake mix", "originalString"=>"1 box Favorite Vanilla or Butter Pound Cake mix", "originalName"=>"Favorite Vanilla or Butter Pound Cake mix", "amount"=>1.0, "unit"=>"box", "meta"=>[], "metaInformation"=>[], "measures"=>{"us"=>{"amount"=>1.0, "unitShort"=>"box", "unitLong"=>"box"}, "metric"=>{"amount"=>1.0, "unitShort"=>"box", "unitLong"=>"box"}}}], steps_data: [{"number"=>1, "step"=>"Preheat oven to the temperature specified for the butter or vanilla pound cake.Assemble the vanilla pound cake per the recipe or mix directions.  To make the brilliant fuchsia heart, add 1/8 teaspoon Wilton Rose coloring to the mix (if desiring a more tame pink, begin to add small amounts dipped from the container with a toothpick, mix and add more if needed; it is very concentrated coloring).", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404644, "name"=>"toothpicks", "image"=>"toothpicks.jpg"}, {"id"=>404784, "name"=>"oven", "image"=>"oven.jpg"}]}, {"number"=>2, "step"=>"Mix incorporating the color uniformly in the batter.Begin adding cherry flavoring by the ½ teaspoon until reaching desired flavor.  Note: I used a natural Cherry flavoring and wanted a strong cherry flavor to stand up to the chocolate in the outer cake so ended up using 1 tablespoon.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>9070, "name"=>"cherries", "image"=>"cherries.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[]}, {"number"=>3, "step"=>"Pour batter into a prepared loaf pan.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404715, "name"=>"loaf pan", "image"=>"loaf-pan.png"}]}, {"number"=>4, "step"=>"Bake as instructed in recipe or mix directions.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[]}, {"number"=>5, "step"=>"Remove, cool and remove from the pan.  Allow to cool completely.Reheat oven to specified temperature for the chocolate pound cake recipe or mix.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404784, "name"=>"oven", "image"=>"oven.jpg"}, {"id"=>404645, "name"=>"frying pan", "image"=>"pan.png"}]}, {"number"=>6, "step"=>"Place cherry pound cake on a cutting board.  Using the depth of the heart cookie cutter as a guide, cut the pound cake into slices the same thickness as the cookie cutter (e.g. my cookie cutter is 1 inch deep so I made slices that were 1 inch thick).", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}, {"id"=>9070, "name"=>"cherries", "image"=>"cherries.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>221429, "name"=>"cookie cutter", "image"=>"cookie-cutters.jpg"}, {"id"=>404716, "name"=>"cutting board", "image"=>"cutting-board.jpg"}]}, {"number"=>7, "step"=>"Place each slice flat on the cutting board and using the cookie cutter cut one heart out of each slice.  Set aside scraps.Butter a loaf pan the same size or larger than the pan used for the cherry pound cake.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}, {"id"=>9070, "name"=>"cherries", "image"=>"cherries.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>221429, "name"=>"cookie cutter", "image"=>"cookie-cutters.jpg"}, {"id"=>404716, "name"=>"cutting board", "image"=>"cutting-board.jpg"}, {"id"=>404715, "name"=>"loaf pan", "image"=>"loaf-pan.png"}]}, {"number"=>8, "step"=>"Place cherry pound cake hearts in the middle of the prepared pan; point down, back-to-back touching each other.Prepare the chocolate pound cake recipe or mix according to the directions.This step is easiest accomplished with a helper!  Begin on one end of the loaf pan, with one person holding the hearts upright on their point, place a spoonful of batter on one side of the first heart and then a spoonful on the opposite of the first heart.  Proceed up the pan in this manner until there is a small amount of batter on either side of all the hearts; this will stabilize the hearts and ensure they stay on their point during baking.  Fill in the remaining batter on both sides and cover the top of the hearts.  Note: the top may be rounded due to the shape of the top of the hearts.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}, {"id"=>9070, "name"=>"cherries", "image"=>"cherries.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404715, "name"=>"loaf pan", "image"=>"loaf-pan.png"}]}, {"number"=>9, "step"=>"Bake the pound cake to the directions for the chocolate pound cake.  Check for doneness earlier than suggested.  Due to the pre-baked cherry pound cake center the pound cake may done earlier than if baking regularly.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}, {"id"=>9070, "name"=>"cherries", "image"=>"cherries.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[]}, {"number"=>10, "step"=>"Remove from oven; allow to cool for 15-20 minutes in the pan on a cooling rack.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>405900, "name"=>"wire rack", "image"=>"wire-rack.jpg"}, {"id"=>404784, "name"=>"oven", "image"=>"oven.jpg"}, {"id"=>404645, "name"=>"frying pan", "image"=>"pan.png"}], "length"=>{"number"=>20, "unit"=>"minutes"}}, {"number"=>11, "step"=>"Remove from pan and cool completely before slicing. Note: I found the gluten free pound cake sliced best after refrigerating. Can be kept in the refrigerator tightly wrapped for up to a week or frozen and then defrosted to be eaten at a later date.In the next Boulder Locavore post will be a recipe to use up the leftover scraps of the Cherry Pound Cake!", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>18133, "name"=>"pound cake", "image"=>"pound-cake.jpg"}, {"id"=>9070, "name"=>"cherries", "image"=>"cherries.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404645, "name"=>"frying pan", "image"=>"pan.png"}]}], photo: "https://spoonacular.com/recipeImages/Hidden-Heart-Valentines-Pound-Cake-522159.jpg"},
