 over: When air bubbles start to bubble up to the surface at the center of the pancakes (about 2-3 minutes), use a flat metal spatula to flip them over.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404642, "name"=>"spatula", "image"=>"spatula-or-turner.jpg"}], "length"=>{"number"=>3, "unit"=>"minutes"}}, {"number"=>13, "step"=>"After a minute, peek under one for doneness. When golden or darker golden brown, they are done.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[]}, {"number"=>14, "step"=>"Note that cooking the second side takes only about half as long as the first side. And the second side doesn't brown as evenly as the first side.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[]}, {"number"=>15, "step"=>"Continue to make the batches of pancakes, putting a little oil or butter on the pan before each batch so the pancakes don't stick.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>1001, "name"=>"butter", "image"=>"butter-sliced.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404645, "name"=>"frying pan", "image"=>"pan.png"}]}, {"number"=>16, "step"=>"Serve immediately.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[]}, {"number"=>17, "step"=>"Serve with butter, maple syrup, and extra blueberries.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>9050, "name"=>"blueberries", "image"=>"blueberries.jpg"}, {"id"=>1001, "name"=>"butter", "image"=>"butter-sliced.jpg"}], "equipment"=>[]}], photo: "https://spoonacular.com/recipeImages/Blueberry-Buttermilk-Pancakes-245589.jpg"},
