=>"mixing bowl", "image"=>"mixing-bowl.jpg"}, {"id"=>404669, "name"=>"sauce pan", "image"=>"sauce-pan.jpg"}]}, {"number"=>2, "step"=>"Pour milk mixture into the flour mixture and with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat until smooth.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>20081, "name"=>"all purpose flour", "image"=>"flour.png"}], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404628, "name"=>"hand mixer", "image"=>"hand-mixer.png"}]}, {"number"=>3, "step"=>"Add the eggs and beat on high for approximately 3 minutes. Stir in orange zest and 1 1/2 cups flour.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>9216, "name"=>"orange zest", "image"=>"orange-zest.png"}, {"id"=>20081, "name"=>"all purpose flour", "image"=>"flour.png"}, {"id"=>1123, "name"=>"egg", "image"=>"egg.png"}], "equipment"=>[], "length"=>{"number"=>3, "unit"=>"minutes"}}, {"number"=>4, "step"=>"Mix well. Dough will be sticky.Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. As you knead the dough, add the remaining 1/2 cup flour a little at a time. You may not need the full amount. Use just enough to make the dough elastic and smooth. Continue to knead for approximately 5 minutes.", "ingredients"=>[{"id"=>20081, "name"=>"all purpose flour", "image"=>"flour.png"}], "equipment"=>[], "length"=>{"number"=>5, "unit"=>"minutes"}}, {"number"=>5, "step"=>"Place dough in a lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease the top. Cover and let rise in a warm place for one hour or until doubled in size.Punch down dough and turn onto a lightly floured surface. Divide the dough in half.Taking one half of the dough, roll out into a 14 x 10-inch triangle. Slice into 2-inch strips lengthwise, then cut those strips in half crosswise (they should measure approx. 7 inches in length). Set aside the outside dough strips that are too small. You'll use these for the tails.", "ingredients"=>[], "equipment"=>[{"id"=>404783, "name"=>"bowl", "image"=>"bowl.jpg"}]}, {"number"=>6, "step"=>"Roll the strips into a long rope about 14-16 inches long.Shape: Lay the rope of dough on the prepared baki